class Solution {
    public int minPartitions(String n) {
        int max = 0;
        for (int i = 0, len = n.length(); i < len; ++i) {
            int d = n.charAt(i) - '0';
            if (d > max) max = d;
            if (max == 9) break;
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The minimum number of deci-binary addends equals the largest digit in the string, because each subtraction of a deci-binary can reduce every digit by at most 1. Scanning the string once to find the maximum digit yields the answer in linear time with constant extra space.

